commons-xml
===========

A Java library for easy XML processing.

This software is part of the Shredzone Commons.

The source code can be found at [GitHub](https://github.com/shred/commons-xml) and is distributed under the terms of [GNU Lesser General Public License Version 3](http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html).

Installation
------------

_commons-xml_ is available at Maven Central. Just add this snippet to your `pom.xml`:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>${project.groupId}</groupId>
  <artifactId>${project.artifactId}</artifactId>
  <version>${project.version}</version>
</dependency>
```

Java Module
-----------

Add this line to your module descriptor:

```java
requires org.shredzone.commons.xml;
```

Dependencies and Requirements
-----------------------------

_commons-xml_ requires at least Java 8, but has no other dependencies.
